title: For Sale:  PWS MK116 Piston AR Upper
postcontent: I am selling a Primary Weapon Systems (PWS) MK116 gas piston operated AR15 upper receiver assembly. It has a 16" government profile 1:8 barrel chambered in 5.56 NATO/.223 Remington, and a monolithic quad rail with multiple quick-detach points. It includes a the complete bolt carrier group (BCG) and VLTOR/BCM Gunfighter charging handle with extended latch. The round count is relatively low, and it has been meticulously maintained by a US Marine. This is a complete upper receiver assembly, but it is not a complete firearm. A lower receiver assembly is required.The PWS piston system operates by a gas piston attached by a rod to the BCG, rather than a gas tube. This keeps the gasses away from the BCG keeping the action clean, cooler, and functional after countless rounds. A piston operated AR15 is exceptionally reliable and requires far less cleaning. This corrects one of the top drawbacks to this awesome weapon platform.www.primaryweapons.com
